{
  "stem": "16442.3",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 272.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "On the road, we passed the B Lager and C Lager and went all the way around, which was a march about a good half an hour each day back on-- you know, each time.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And we saw the people.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "Matter of fact, that [?",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "C ?] Lager was the worst.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "They got the least amount of food, the worst clothing, and the most people went to the crematorium from there.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "When we marched from our work, back and forth-- by the way, the place where I worked was called Brzezinka.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "That was the name of it.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "And they gave us a white kerchief.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "We had to have our head covered with a white kerchief.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "And this is how we marched.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "That was how they recognized us, who we were and where we were going.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "Now each time we would come back at night, from the [?",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "C ?] Lager, the people were lined up by the wires, by the electric wires, begging for food.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "Now we used to hide certain foods, take a-- a piece of rag or a kerchief or something, and we would throw things over, because we had food.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "People who came, their luggage, their packages were-- there were food in them.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "We used to throw things over the fence.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "And then the SS came and wanted to the punish us and kill us.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "And we had to tell-- to tell who did it.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "Nobody ever, ever said one word who threw the packages.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "And we used to do that every day.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] They-- [SIGHS] Only thing was, in this is terribly sad kommando where I was working-- well, I had enough food.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 35,
      "text": "I had enough to drink.",
      "word_count": 5
    }
  ],
